Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about dialogue state tracking in task-oriented dialogue systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under this category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as DST is an essential component of AI-powered dialogue systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed model uses multiple encoder-decoder architecture, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the challenges and solutions in developing a dialogue system. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also possible as the paper deals with extracting information from heterogeneous texts.
